tment of\ntuberculosis disease. The buildings\nwere erected by the army for that\nparticular purpose and are superior\nto most of those in base camps\nTwo of the wards will 'be remodel-,\ned; and some additional buildings\nwill be erected for the use of the\nstaff, especially the married staff, J\nfor whom 110 accommodations now\nexist. j\nThe present patients will probably I\nremain, if the hospital equipment\ncan be taken over with them. The j\nnurse's, except those who wish to\ntake accrued leave, will remain.\nThe hospital in New York, vari j\nousiy known as the Hoff General\nhospital and the 17. S. Debarkation j\nhospital, Is at Fax Hills, about ten'\nminutes walk from- the New York\nCity ferry station' at Stapleton, Stat\nen Island. It will be continued as\na general hospital with a capacity\nof about .100 beds. Dr. J. O. Cobb\nrecently in charge\" of all Public\nHealth Service activities at Chica\ngo, will be in charge. By reason of\nits proximity to New York City this\nhospital has available the best con\nsuttation facilities in the country.\nlis\nA\nClcp Scratching\nEczerra Can Be Cured\nZ!nsut has broundt rMof to\nMm u-HnlM iuid rured tltoutfan'ln\ninure Tti th-wl utiti'ifut'rtn it tiiia\nj wl'tte, inirio.-n, cool if is, soothing\nh' 'inr iiowivn.\nZeriEat is the remilt of year of\nMui.y by a m rt.il.wt,\nII you havtt the H y, waly eriii\ntlun :-k for I r y 7t-n:A. If you\nhnvp (h wateiy skin ak lur\nMit -St ZIIHUI.\nSo hy tfve drunists rvery\nwliur. 1-ltM'ral jar for 7.r eta.\nTte Zecsal Co. of Qk'ahoma Cit, Ok!a.\nNela Darling. Prest.\nOWL DRUG STORE\nWW\nl.', s. V\nlimm If 1\nWher the Sea Sand Sings.\n\"Slnping sands' are found In Tin-n-nll.\nRy clapping be sand hetweer\nthe hands n faint hooting noise Is pro\nduced. But the sounds are greatly In\ntensified hv putilng 11 intimity in a bag\nand slamming it about.\nRADIATOR\nTROUBLES\n.re our specially, tlie repair\nand overhaul by us assures ytuir\nmotor's ruiiiiiny cooly ami at\nfull efficii'.i.'v.\n\nD